race.comment: Tough race. MISS LEANA (11) was well below best last time and has since been scratched at the barrier at the end of last month. Overall record is consistent and form is good for this. Gets a chance to atone. BEEN A SECRET (2) was a solid fourth here two back then well off best in tougher company last time. Returns to her home track and off the low draw will take catching. OCEAN JOY (7) is a former NSW galloper with a consistent record resuming on a new home track for the new yard. Trip suits and best figures stack up. BUTT HEADS (3) has been freshened since finishing third here last time. Best form is here and looks a leading chance. TORONESS (9) was in great form before a spell and has won a trial leading into this. Drawn the inside and will take catching.
